events.title: Responsible AI Development with Trevor Angle
events.description: Experts agree that the intelligence level of AI is going to continue increasing exponentially, and that it may pass humans in general intelligence within our lifetimes. What are the implications of this? What precautions do we need to take as responsible developers? Is it all just science fiction? These questions and more will be discussed in this talk.

events.title: Garmin International
events.description: Garmin Engineer Chris Foster will be giving a compnay overview of Garmin along with his experiences as an engineer in the technical industry.

events.title: What to do over the summer?
events.description: Looking for ideas on what to do over the summer? Eric Peterson, SoDAâ€™s new Vice President will be giving a presentation on just that. Eric will go over some ideas on what you should do with your free time in order to help grow your skills to ensure that you stand out when applying for future jobs and internships.

events.title: Flapjack Fest and Shirt Giveaway
events.description: For SoDA's last event of the school year, come celebrate with our flapjack fest tradition! Hang out with other SoDA members, eat some pancakes, and participate in our raffle for a chance to win a Nintendo Switch and a Roku 4K! We will also be handing out free SoDA shirts.

events.title: First SoDA Meeting
events.description: What is SoDA and can I drink it? Join us for our first meeting of the semester! We will outline the layout of SoDA and let you know about our upcoming events.

events.title: Board Game Night!
events.description: Finish off the first week of school and play some board games with SoDA! Feel free to bring some games of your own!

events.title: GitHub Basics!
events.description: Want to show off your personal projects in a professional way? Keep hearing about GitHub, and all its' benefits? Join us for a talk on git and learn what exactly git is, how to use it, and how you can use it to improve your resume!

events.title: Amazon Tech Talk
events.description: Amazon will be hosting our first industry event of the school year focused on scaling, throttling and building resilient systems.

events.title: Technical Interview Workshop
events.description: Get a head start on your first technical interview with our round of mock interview questions! SoDA Officers will be here to guide you through a typical coding interview setting.

events.title: Resume Review Workshop
events.description: Come by SoDA and get your resume reviewed by Microsoft! Get useful feedback and tips on how to improve your resume so you can get your dream internship/job!

events.title: Goldman Sachs HackerRank Tutorial
events.description: Come by SoDA for a technical interview prep by Goldman Sachs! Learn more about Goldman Sachs and the HackerRank platform and how you can use it to ace your technical interviews!

events.title: Career Fair Follow Up
events.description: Reflect on the career fair and the next steps to take. Also practice some technical and behavioral questions for your interviews coming up!

events.title: The Benefits of Learning React Native
events.description: Learn how to become a web developer and a mobile developer at the same time with React Native!

events.title: Deloitte Technical Workshop
events.description: Come by to participate in a technical workshop on Tech Trends hosted by Deloitte! Learn about Intelligent Interfaces, AI-Fueled Organizations, & the Connectivity of Tomorrow and how they play a role in technology consulting.
